headline.main: A Heroine Arrived--The Young Wife who took Neptune's Car around Cape Horn.

docs.lead_paragraph: Among the passengers from California, who arrived by the steamer George Law, on Saturday, there was an invalid who had to be borne from the vessel to his hotel upon a litter. By his side, superintending movement, was a young lady, of prepossessing person, but with a countenance care-worn and anxious from long-watching.
docs.abstract: Her heroic conduct on the Ship Neptunes' Car

docs.lead_paragraph: East Brooklyn Lectures. The Franklin-avenue Presbyterian Church Course of Lectures was concluded last Wednesday evening--a quite successful course, we understand. The last two lectures were delivered by Prof. HOWARD CHOSBY--Subject: Priest-Kings of Europe and Asia, and Mr. J. H. SUYDAM--Subject: Fashion. The money raised by tickets goes to support and improve the Sabbath School in connection with the Church.

docs.lead_paragraph: From the Europa's mails, which reached this city last evening, we have additional details of the China news. The authorities of Canton had apologized to the Americans for firing at their boat's crew and insulting their flag--giving as an excuse that it was a mistake-and this, it was believed, would be accepted.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; Rents. BOARD OF ALDERMEN. Gas in yorkville and Harlem. Councilmen's Committee on Finance.

docs.lead_paragraph: Rents they say are to be higher for residences after May than ever. by from $15 to $50. To get sin gle houses for $350, $100, or even $500, in anything like a pleasant part of the City, was almost impossi ble yeas ago, but henceforth the $400 people must consent to live with other families in their houses, orgo across the water to Brooklyn or Jersey.

docs.lead_paragraph: By the European at Halifax, we received three days' later intelligence from Europe. The Indian mail had been received in London, with details -of the capture of Bushire. The place had been proclaimed British territory and a free port. We have no confirmation of the statement that Persia had submitted to the demands of Great Britain, and it is yet received with doubt.

headline.main: ARRIVAL OF THE EMPIRE CITY.; News from Havana-Grand Military Review--Shipping and Commercial Intelligence.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Empire City, Capt. S. P. Grihm, left New Orleans at 8 A. M. the 5th, and arrived at Havana at 1 P. M. on the 8th-coaled-transferred her California mails and passengers to the Granada for Aspinwall, and left on the 10th at 10 3/4 o'clock for this port.
